<br>
The problem with casters is, if you get into melee range with one, the <b>ONLY</b> way they can cast a spell is to quickcast or to spam the cast key until the spell goes through. The chance to interrupt a caster is 99%, and when you do managed to interrrupt them, they can't even attempt to cast again for 5 seconds. This leaves the caster dead.<br>
<br>
Mythic, instead of making interruptions less intrusive gave casters bladeturn and absorption buffs then went about bolstering their damage. When the problem was simply without range, a caster is dead--PvE or RvR.<br>
<br>
Then epic armor came along and casters have decent survivability, but still if someone gets into melee range of them it's as if they lose all their spec points because the only spell they can cast is the one they quickcast.<br>
<br>
Root problems of Class types:<br>
<br>
Heavy Melee: Cannot physically stop anyone<br>
Casters: Spell interrupted too easily; melee cannot physically protect casters<br>
Healers: Combat is still a bit too fast for heals; melee cannot physically protect healers<br>
Light Melee: Often outdamaged by Heavy Melee, yet still defensively inferior<br>
Archers: Stupidly high miss and fumble rates with bows<br>
Assassins: Hidden attacks are vastly inferior to Heavy Melee no-opening styles and most ranged attacks -- rapidly becoming light melee with poison and stealth. Why not just combine light melee and assassins into one class and stop the suffering?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushareefromtristan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShareeFromTristan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/23/02 12:26:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3781.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> This whole 'you whine got LA nerfed' is ridiculous.<br>
<br>
I do not believe any amount of whining and nerf cries will actually make a nerf happen. Only thing it does is direct mythic's attention to the 'point of whine'. If, and only if, the examination shows something is wrong, a nerf will come.<br>
<br>
Example: I hear 'You Infiltrators whined about LA and got it nerfed!'<br>
<br>
What in reality happened is that a lot of people complained about doublefrost damage(and not just infiltrators), mythic heard the complaints, looked at logs, thought 'hmm, the damage is kinda high, lets take a look at it...'<br>
<br>
And then '... gosh, we had the damage set wrong the whole time, it should be that on an anytime style, not a reactionary style like it is now!'<br>
<br>
Then, they set the DF damage to the correct type(anytime) which reduced the style damage (and STILL not to where it should be, mind you), NOT because someone whined about it, but because it was simply set wrong.<br>
<br>
So dont go around accussing infiltrators because they(along with others) pointed out a flaw in mythics code.<br>
<br>
<br>
