mage are easy to understand.  To be honest, after the fix to it, I can't understand why people keep saying it needs to be back where it was.  The reason they gave was perfectly reasonable, and made sense.  If peoples' complaint is that it is reduced more than the 3% they said it was, I can understand that.  That should be addressed.  If its damage is less than other use-anytime styles then THAT should be looked at.  If the only complaint is that the damage is lower, well, too bad.<br>
<br>
Other changes however DO come from pure whining.  The one-shot nerf is a PERFECT example of that.  If it wasn't for a cacophany of whining from many players, assassins would still be one-shotting people.  They made a change that caused one-shots to be &quot;inadvertently&quot; fixed.  Ok fine, I'll accept that.  But the only reason it STAYED &quot;fixed&quot; was because people whined that it should. <p>-Aurra Sing-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubalorgafdan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balor Gafdan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/23/02 9:07:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3781.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.camelotherald.com/guilds/nightshade.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Nudges the post back ON topic</span><hr size=1> Buffbots.<br>
<br>
Well, the many suggestions I have seen to fix this problem are all great and worthy of a look, however, the root of the issue is this.<br>
<br>
Do we want to go back to EQ style buffs?<br>
<br>
Think about it?  Mythic ( love the game, much better than verant ) has in the past, taken the easy route to fix things.  This is to be expected, it makes good buisness sense to spend as little time on a fix as possible but still ensuring a fix.  Same results, less money spent.<br>
<br>
There will be no range limit.  Which would be easier to code, a range limit, or a time limit?<br>
<br>
There will be a TIME limit.  I for one, hated this in EQ, and I will hate it here.  It is inevitable that something like this is in the works at Mythic.  As so many of you have pointed out, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   the squeeky wheel gets the grease </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and people are indeed squeaking.<br>
<br>
My wife plays a bard, blue buffs are great, will she let me bot her? No.  Hell, personally, I would feel dirty, cheap, as if my kills were made simply because I had buffs and not because I have the ability to accomplish such on my own.<br>
<br>
Those are my own set of morals.  They can't be forced upon anyone who USES a buffbot, but eventually, Mythic will limit their effectiveness.  Precedence assures us of that.<br>
<br>
<br>
/wink  Nostredamus didn't have nothing on me /wink<br>
<br>
Hey, if that other guy can make predictions, so can I.<br>
